The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Surge in gem exports

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, April 20: The country?s gem and jewellery exports jumped by 29.3 per cent to touch the $15.7-billion mark during the financial year ended March 31, 2005. The corresponding figure for 2003-04 was $12.1 billion.

 Exports of cut and polished diamonds during the year grew by 29.6 per cent to $11.2 billion from $8.6 billion in the previous year. There has been an impressive 42.2 per cent growth in the jewellery segment, which increased its share in the overall gem and jewellery sector. 




